#!perl
use strict;
use warnings;
use App::PPE;
App::PPE->new_with_options(@ARGV)->run;

__END__

=encoding utf-8

=head1 NAME

ppe - Prettify Perl Error messages

=head1 SYNOPSIS

  % perl ~/foo.pl 2>&1 | ppe
  foo.pl:5: [WARN] (W) Use of uninitialized value in warn

=head1 DESCRIPTION

L<ppe> is a prettifier for Perl error messages.

=head1 SEE ALSO

L<perldiag>
